<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<kml xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:gx="http://www.google.com/kml/ext/2.2" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2">
  <Document>
    <name>StylesDoc.kml</name>
    
    <!--

To reference a style from within the KML document's <Placemark>s with just a # element
id, add a needed <StyleMap> to the KML docment(s) that will be using the style:

<StyleMap id="c">
  <Pair>
    <key>normal</key>
    <styleUrl>StylesDoc.kml#controlArea</styleUrl>
  </Pair>
  <Pair>
    <key>highlight</key>
    <styleUrl>StylesDoc.kml#controlArea</styleUrl>
  </Pair>
</StyleMap>

<StyleMap id="h">
  <Pair>
    <key>normal</key>
    <styleUrl>StylesDoc.kml#highway</styleUrl>
  </Pair>
  <Pair>
    <key>highlight</key>
    <styleUrl>StylesDoc.kml#highway</styleUrl>
  </Pair>
</StyleMap>

Then, update each <Placemark> in the KML document(s) to reference a corresponding <StyleMap>:

<styleUrl>#c</styleUrl>

or

<styleUrl>#h</styleUrl>

    -->
    <Style id="controlArea">
      <LineStyle>
<!--         <color>99520019</color>
 -->        <color>ff0000ff</color>
        <width>1.5</width>
      </LineStyle>
      <PolyStyle>
        <color>19ff0056</color>
      </PolyStyle>
    </Style>

    <Style id="highway">
      <LineStyle>
<!--         <color>99520019</color>
 -->        <color>ff0000ff</color>
        <width>2</width>
      </LineStyle>
    </Style>
    
  </Document>
</kml>
